|11,73
     A WHILE loop repeats a number of instructions until a given condition
becomes false.  If the condition is false to begin with, the instructions
will never be executed.

while Examples:
     i := 0;
     while i <= 10 do begin
         writeln(i,i*i,i*i*i);
         i := i + 1;
         end;
|mFor more, choose
|iDo nothing,nop
|iRepeat Loops,Hpnode/repeat_loop
|iBoolean values,Hpsymbol/boolean
|p
